des:
If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us via email : smart@statusinternationaluk.co.uk

You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show after connecting Alexa to your Status Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our Status Smart app in android or iOS app market;
(2). Register one Status Smart account in our Status Smart app;
(3). You need to have some Status smart product devices in hand;
(4). Configure these product devices in our Status Smart app and change to an appropriate name for your devices which will be used in Status Smart skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, iOS or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search Status Smart skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of Status Smart, and you'll be navigated to the Status Smart login page;
(9). Input your Status Smart account username and password, you'll be redirected to the success page;
(10). Now the setup is complete, your Status Smart product is now ready for use. 

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, discover my devices.”
“Alexa, turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, brighten the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, dim the bedroom light to 50%.”
"Alexa, set bedroom light to green."
"Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white."

Currently this skill supports products:
smart light,
smart socket, 
smart camera,
more to come....
